A vintage-style illustration of a person standing on a seaside cliff, gazing intently through old brass binoculars toward a calm horizon on the left, while behind them on the right, an enormous dramatic wave curls and rises, about to crash down. The scene uses muted sepia and ocean blue tones with a weathered, aged photograph aesthetic. The composition emphasizes the stark contrast between the figure's oblivious calm focus in the wrong direction and the imminent force of nature approaching unseen from behind.
